<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 2:44PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Madison and southeastern Beaverhead Counties through 330 PM MDT...
At 244 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monida, or 23 miles northwest of Idmon, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Monida and Monida Pass.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southwestern Montana.</instruction>
